sequenceDiagram
    participant Tools as Tools<br/>(starboard-server)
    participant LogParser as Log Parser<br/>(starboard-log-parser)
    participant DBFS as Databricks DBFS
    participant Agent as Agent System
    
    Note over Tools: Tool needs Spark event log analysis
    
    Tools->>Tools: resolve_job() identifies<br/>need for log parsing
    
    Tools->>DBFS: Get log path from job run<br/>GET /api/2.0/jobs/runs/get-output
    
    DBFS-->>Tools: Log path:<br/>dbfs:/cluster-logs/eventlog.gz
    
    Note over Tools: Step 1: Initialize Log Parser
    
    Tools->>LogParser: create_spark_application(<br/>  log_path="dbfs:/cluster-logs/eventlog.gz"<br/>)
    
    Note over LogParser: Step 2: Read Log File
    
    LogParser->>DBFS: Read event log file<br/>GET /api/2.0/dbfs/read<br/>?path=dbfs:/cluster-logs/eventlog.gz
    
    DBFS-->>LogParser: Compressed event log data
    
    Note over LogParser: Step 3: Parse Events
    
    LogParser->>LogParser: Decompress log file<br/>(gzip)
    
    LogParser->>LogParser: Parse Spark events:<br/>- SparkListenerJobStart<br/>- SparkListenerTaskEnd<br/>- SparkListenerStageCompleted<br/>- etc.
    
    LogParser->>LogParser: Build SparkApplication model:<br/>- Jobs<br/>- Stages<br/>- Tasks<br/>- Metrics
    
    Note over LogParser: Step 4: Return Parsed Data
    
    LogParser-->>Tools: SparkApplication {<br/>  jobs: [...],<br/>  stages: [...],<br/>  tasks: [...],<br/>  metrics: {...}<br/>}
    
    Note over Tools: Step 5: Extract Metrics
    
    Tools->>Tools: Extract performance metrics:<br/>- Task duration<br/>- Shuffle read/write<br/>- Data skew<br/>- Resource utilization
    
    Tools-->>Agent: ToolResult {<br/>  job_data: {...},<br/>  spark_metrics: {...},<br/>  performance_issues: [...]<br/>}
    
    Note over Agent: Agent uses metrics for<br/>optimization recommendations
    
    Note over Tools: Log parser integration complete<br/>Enables detailed Spark analysis

